<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7600] Schema change notifications sent for no-op DDL statements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7600</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When schema changes are made with &lt;tt&gt;IF [NOT] EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; conditions, we return schema change messages (and push out schema change notifications) even if the &lt;tt&gt;IF [NOT] EXISTS&lt;/tt&gt; condition makes it a no-op.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This results in extra work for native protocol drivers, which typically wait for schema agreement and refresh their schema metadata when schema changes occur.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12729241">CASSANDRA-7600</key>
